{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-04-13T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"When the lights go down, the universe puts on a show. The image of the Milky Way glowing above Anza-Borrego Desert State Park captures that feeling perfectly. As California's largest state park and a certified International Dark-Sky Association Dark Sky Park, Anza-Borrego offers some of the clearest night skies in the country. On cloudless evenings, the heavens fill with planets, star clusters and the pale river of our home galaxy, a sight long lost to many city dwellers.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BorregoStars_ROW1985712263_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BorregoStars_ROW1985712263_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Milky Way over Anza-Borrego Desert State Park, California, United States","Copyright":"© Kevin Key/Slworking)/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260413_BorregoStars\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Anza+Borrego+Desert+State+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260413_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260413_BorregoStars"},"Ssd":"20260413","Name":"BorregoStars","Market":"ROW","Hash":"1985712263","FullDateString":"13 de abr. de 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Look up on a clear night and a bright moving star might actually be the International Space Station. That spirit of exploration lives on aboard the ISS, a laboratory where Earth never quite leaves the view. From the space station, astronauts photograph glowing city grids, curling auroras and lightning storms streaking through the atmosphere. The station orbits about 400 kilometres above Earth and circles the planet every 90 minutes, delivering up to 16 sunrises and sunsets each day.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpaceTrails_ROW1837084616_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpaceTrails_ROW1837084616_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"City lights streak below, taken from the International Space Station","Copyright":"© NASA","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260412_SpaceTrails\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Space+Station&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260412_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260412_SpaceTrails"},"Ssd":"20260412","Name":"SpaceTrails","Market":"ROW","Hash":"1837084616","FullDateString":"12 de abr. de 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"A beach born from fire rarely does so subtly, yet Papagayo Beach manages exactly that. The shoreline we see today rests on the southern edge of Lanzarote, one of Spain's Canary Islands. Tropical fantasy? More like volcanic precision. Millions of years ago, this land rose in successive layers of basalt and ash thrust upward by submarine eruptions.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.PlayaPapagayo_ROW1699824695_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.PlayaPapagayo_ROW1699824695_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Papagayo Beach, Lanzarote, Canary Islands, Spain","Copyright":"© Gavin Hellier/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260411_PlayaPapagayo\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Lanzarote+Canary+Islands+Spain&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260411_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260411_PlayaPapagayo"},"Ssd":"20260411","Name":"PlayaPapagayo","Market":"ROW","Hash":"1699824695","FullDateString":"11 de abr. de 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Ever caught siblings plotting? In Karula National Park, Estonia, it looks as though these two red fox kits froze mid-conspiracy, their expressions mirrored in curiosity and caution. They're not just springtime fluff; they're apprentices in survival. Born in litters averaging four to six kits, foxes grow quickly, their underground den becoming a wrestling ring, classroom and testing ground. Older kits often help feed, guard and teach the younger ones, turning play into practice and mischief into muscle memory.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.FoxSiblings_ROW1554598734_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.FoxSiblings_ROW1554598734_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Two young red foxes at Karula National Park, Estonia","Copyright":"© Sven Zacek/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260410_FoxSiblings\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Karula+National+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260410_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260410_FoxSiblings"},"Ssd":"20260410","Name":"FoxSiblings","Market":"ROW","Hash":"1554598734","FullDateString":"10 de abr. de 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Water spills in clean lines at Sgwd yr Eira, one of South Wales' most distinctive waterfalls. Its Welsh name means 'Waterfall of Snow,' referring to the pale curtain of water sliding over the rock face. What sets this waterfall apart is access. A narrow path leads visitors behind the falling water, immersing them in sound, light and movement at close range. Sgwd yr Eira lies within Bannau Brycheiniog National Park, often called 'Waterfall Country' for its network of rivers and falls carved into wooded gorges. Well-marked trails connect this waterfall to others along the River Hepste, making it a popular stop on longer hikes. Above the valleys, the landscape opens into rolling moorland and long ridgelines where upland paths are shaped by wind and changing weather. These contrasts define the Bannau Brycheiniog, where open, exposed uplands give way to sheltered water, tying the landscape together.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.WalesWaterfall_ROW4607856907_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.WalesWaterfall_ROW4607856907_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Sgwd yr Eira waterfall, Bannau Brycheiniog National Park, Wales","Copyright":"© Guy Edwardes/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260409_WalesWaterfall\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bannau+Brycheiniog+National+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260409_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260409_WalesWaterfall"},"Ssd":"20260409","Name":"WalesWaterfall","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4607856907","FullDateString":"9 de abr. de 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Seattle's waterfront seems suspended between sea and sky as soft light settles on the horizon. The city is named after Chief Si'ahl, a leader of the Duwamish and Suquamish peoples, whose legacy remains important to the region's identity. Steep streets lead down to piers that sweep across Elliott Bay. Rising above the shoreline, the Space Needle stands out as the city's most recognisable landmark. Pike Place Market, founded in 1907, overlooks the waterfront and continues to anchor daily life and long-held traditions.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SeattleSunrise_ROW1229095485_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SeattleSunrise_ROW1229095485_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Seattle, Washington, United States","Copyright":"© Jim Patterson/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260408_SeattleSunrise\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Seattle&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260408_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260408_SeattleSunrise"},"Ssd":"20260408","Name":"SeattleSunrise","Market":"ROW","Hash":"1229095485","FullDateString":"8 de abr. de 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The beaver—buck-toothed, paddle-tailed and famously industrious—has been reshaping freshwater landscapes for millions of years. With their iron-reinforced orange incisors, these skilled rodents cut down trees and build dams that slow the flow of water, improve its quality and create wetlands that support a remarkable diversity of life. Their sturdy lodges, made of branches and mud, have underwater entrances that protect them from predators and keep their families safe.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BeaverPortrait_ROW1082400008_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BeaverPortrait_ROW1082400008_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Beaver, Germany","Copyright":"© Andyworks/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260407_BeaverPortrait\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Beaver+rodent&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260407_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260407_BeaverPortrait"},"Ssd":"20260407","Name":"BeaverPortrait","Market":"ROW","Hash":"1082400008","FullDateString":"7 de abr. de 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"In south-eastern Utah, USA, Canyonlands National Park reveals a vast, rugged landscape shaped over millions of years by the Colorado and Green rivers. Established in 1964, the park protects a maze of canyons, mesas and buttes carved into layers of ancient rock. Divided into districts such as Island in the Sky and The Needles, it offers sweeping views that shift with the light from dawn to dusk.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SunsetKiva_ROW8130256678_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SunsetKiva_ROW8130256678_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Sunset in Canyonlands National Park, Moab, Utah, United States","Copyright":"© Jason Hatfield/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260420_SunsetKiva\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Canyonlands+National+Park+Moab&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260420_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260420_SunsetKiva"},"Ssd":"20260420","Name":"SunsetKiva","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8130256678","FullDateString":"20 de abr. de 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"From above, Brazil's Mirror Beach looks like a watercolour you can walk into. Pale cliffs, reefs stitched into the shoreline and a mosaic of tide pools that, at low tide, reflect the sky and clouds so clearly that the beach earns its name. Tucked into Bahia, a north-eastern state on the Atlantic coast, it sits between small fishing villages in the city of Porto Seguro. Access follows dirt roads and short trails—a natural crowd-control system that keeps the vibe intimate. For years, it stayed off the map, known only through word of mouth, until the 1990s brought it onto travellers' radars.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TranBA_ROW7860007942_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TranBA_ROW7860007942_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Mirror Beach, Porto Seguro, Bahia, Brazil","Copyright":"© Marcelo Nacinovic/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260419_TranBA\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bahia+Brazil&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260419_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260419_TranBA"},"Ssd":"20260419","Name":"TranBA","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7860007942","FullDateString":"19 de abr. de 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Rolling hills in Tuscany, Italy, feel like they've been styled with intent—soft curves, neat rows of vines and those tall, unmistakable cypress trees. Have you ever noticed how the landscape seems to change colour with the seasons? Spring brings bright greens and wildflowers, summer turns fields golden and autumn deepens everything into warm, earthy tones.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ToscanaSpring_ROW0859656735_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ToscanaSpring_ROW0859656735_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Rolling hills of Tuscany, Italy","Copyright":"© Andyworks/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260418_ToscanaSpring\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Tuscany+Italy&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260418_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260418_ToscanaSpring"},"Ssd":"20260418","Name":"ToscanaSpring","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0859656735","FullDateString":"18 de abr. de 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"When the sun sets, a mysterious animal takes over the skies: bats. With more than 1,400 species found on every continent except Antarctica, they play a vital role in keeping ecosystems in balance. They have existed for over 50 million years, and while only three species feed on blood, the vast majority rely on insects, fruit, nectar or pollen, helping to control pests and support plant life.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.FlyingFoxMom_ROW6773514789_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.FlyingFoxMom_ROW6773514789_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Grey-headed flying fox carrying her pup, Yarra Bend Park, Australia","Copyright":"© Doug Gimesy/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260417_FlyingFoxMom\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Grey-headed+flying+fox&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260417_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260417_FlyingFoxMom"},"Ssd":"20260417","Name":"FlyingFoxMom","Market":"ROW","Hash":"6773514789","FullDateString":"17 de abr. de 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Each spring, Skagit Valley in Washington, United States, transforms into a patchwork of colour that celebrates the arrival of bloom season. Throughout April, visitors explore tulip gardens and farmland lined with vibrant rows of flowers, all framed by mountain views. The valley's fertile soils, shaped by centuries of sediment from the Skagit River, make it one of the most productive agricultural regions in the Pacific Northwest. Tulips arrived here in the early twentieth century when farmers realised the cool springs and long daylight hours were ideal for growing bulbs.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SkagitTulips_ROW2420005352_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SkagitTulips_ROW2420005352_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Skagit Valley Tulip Fields, Washington, United States","Copyright":"© Alan Majchrowicz/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260416_SkagitTulips\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Skagit+Valley+Washington&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260416_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260416_SkagitTulips"},"Ssd":"20260416","Name":"SkagitTulips","Market":"ROW","Hash":"2420005352","FullDateString":"16 de abr. de 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Set in the foothills and front ranges of the Canadian Rockies, Kananaskis Country stretches across a vast network of protected valleys, dense forests and alpine peaks. Located in Alberta, the region was formally established in 1978, uniting several provincial parks and protected areas under a shared vision of conservation. Clear rivers cut through limestone cliffs, while spruce and pine forests rise toward high mountain passes.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AlbertaSnowMts_ROW3394188074_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AlbertaSnowMts_ROW3394188074_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Pine trees reflected in the Forgetmenot Pond in Kananaskis Country, Alberta, Canada","Copyright":"© chinaface/Getty images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260415_AlbertaSnowMts\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Kananaskis+Country+Alberta&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260415_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260415_AlbertaSnowMts"},"Ssd":"20260415","Name":"AlbertaSnowMts","Market":"ROW","Hash":"3394188074","FullDateString":"15 de abr. de 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Sea anemones may look like underwater flowers, but they're actually animals—close relatives of jellyfish and corals. Anchored to rocks or reefs, they use a sticky base and a crown of waving tentacles armed with tiny stingers to capture passing prey. Those stings can paralyse small fish, yet one famous neighbour is immune.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.OcellarisClownfish_ROW2121702907_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.OcellarisClownfish_ROW2121702907_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Common clownfish in a sea anemone, Raja Ampat Islands, Indonesia","Copyright":"© Magnus Lundgren/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260414_OcellarisClownfish\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Sea+anemone&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260414_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260414_OcellarisClownfish"},"Ssd":"20260414","Name":"OcellarisClownfish","Market":"ROW","Hash":"2121702907","FullDateString":"14 de abr. de 2026"}],"LocStrings":{"LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD":"Imagen del día","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD_LEARN_MORE":"Más información","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_DONATE_NOW":"Donar ahora","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_FACT":"Sabías que:","LOC_HOMEPAGE_GALLERY_CARD_TITLE":"Imágenes recientes de la página principal","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_GALLERY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Imagen de la página principal del {0}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_TITLE":"En este día en la historia","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Este día en {0}, {1}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_SHARE_TOOLTIP":"Compartir la página principal de Bing de hoy","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERDOWNLOAD_TOOLTIP":"Descarga la imagen. Solo se puede usar como papel tapiz.","LOC_MUSCARD_DOWNLOAD_LINK":"Descarga esta imagen","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERNOTAVAILABLE":"Esta imagen no está disponible para su descarga como fondo de pantalla.","LOC_HOMEPAGE_INFO_TEXT":"Información","LOC_BING_WP_APP_LINK":"https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linki